ownedComment.body: Primary roles: Agents that are directly involved with the exchange of information. Secondary roles: Agents only mentioned in the documents but not really involved in the information manipulation & exchange. Note: The context may change the roles primacy. Note: There is a mixture of pre/post-award roles. Perhaps a distinction shall be done. Note: Perhaps no role hierarchy is necessary.

Note: Supplier is out of discussion. It is a third party. We do not care who provides these service or products we care with whom business is done.
PEPPOL - Invoice: The supplier is the legal person or organization who provides a product and/or service.
PEPPOL - Order: The supplier is the legal person or organisation who provides a product or service. Examples of supplier roles: seller, despatch party, creditor, economic operator.
Needs to be aligned with eCatalogue in order to chose a codelist to be used.

We need codes for: https://docs.peppol.eu/poacc/upgrade-3/2022-Q4/codelist/UNCL1001_T01/
220 code is plain Order.

If contractually agreed, the Seller also may respond to the order, changing details that are acceptable by the Buyer. -- If an order is accepted with change, the buyer and seller need to have an agreement between them regarding the processing of the changed order, i.e when is a contract concluded and when can the items be shipped.
Proposal: If the order response is "Change" then the Buyer will create (instanciate) a new order implementing the changes and superseding the previously sent order.

A Role of an Agent who transfers the ownership of the Procurement results (goods, services or works) to the Buyer.
Additional information: A Role of an Agent that sells a Procurement Result (goods, services or work) to a Buyer. The Seller is bound by a Contract i.e. it has legal responsibility. The Seller may or may not be the same as the Supplier. The Seller may or may not issue the Invoice. The Seller may or may not be the owner of the credit owed by the Buyer.
WG acceptance 08/09/2022

A Role of an Agent that receives the Shipment of the Procurement (service, goods or works) and who is taking possession.
Additional information: The Role is carried out by the Customer or on behalf of the Customer. The possession of the goods does not necessary imply ownership. The Consignee may be the end-user or the beneficiary.
(Consignee) Definition from PEPPOL Despatch: The Consignee is the person or Organisation to which the products will be shipped and who is taking possession. The Role is carried out by the Customer or on behalf of the Customer.
WG approval: 21/02/2023

A formal request of the Buyer to the Seller specifying the goods, services or works to be delivered.
Additional Information: A Buyer submits an Order for delivery of goods, services or works to a Seller.
WG approval 23/04/2023
